Create a Meta Ads Data Stream for Segment Intelligence

To connect your Meta Ads data, create a data stream and then map the fields in Data Cloud

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience	Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To manage Data Cloud:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
To create a Meta Ads data stream:	Data Cloud Admin permission set

Keep in mind that the stream you create is for the third-party connection selected on the Segment Intelligence setup page.

In Data Cloud, create a Meta Ads data stream.
From the App Launcher, find and select Data Cloud.
In the Data Streams tab, click New.
Select the Meta Ads connector, and then click Next.
Select the connection that you selected in the setup page.
Select an object. These are the required objects for Meta Ads.
Adset Level Performance
Adset Level Conversion
Audiences
Adset Level Audience Targeting
Click Next.
Under Data Lake Object, make sure New Data Lake Object is selected.
Select all the supported fields.
NOTE

When mapping the Event Date field, enter a date and time. The data type changes to DateTime.

Click Next.
Select the data space you selected on the Segment Intelligence setup page.
For Refresh Mode, click Incremental.
Select a Record Modified Date-time.
Set the frequency to daily and set a time.
Click Deploy.
Repeat the above steps for all the required objects.
To sync your data, click Validate on the setup page.
